Notes about “tight compaction” and objective design

Even with bbox area in objective, you can get “dead corridors” because:

bbox area stops improving once it’s limited by largest block dimension(s)

optimizer has no incentive to reduce internal voids afterward

Your new deadspace_B penalty fixes exactly that by pushing blocks to remove gaps after overlap is gone.

Important: what you get and what you don’t (by design)

✅ Hot-path stays fast:

compute_all() adds a linear scan and a small row loop only.

No polygon extraction in optimizer loop.

✅ UI gets polygons:

computed on-demand for the selected iteration

✅ No overlap vs deadspace tradeoff:

deadspace is strictly gated by overlap threshold

⚠️ Polygon accuracy is grid-based (finite-step):

controlled by expected_params.deadspace_cell_size

smaller cell → more accurate polygons, more work per slider update (not per iteration)
